metadata.name: T-SHIRT LAKE
metadata.description:
The three sister lakes of Brighton, Utah which I have dubbed as T-Shirt Lake, because of the close resemblance of a shirt in the first lake seen in this image. 

After a breathtaking drive up Big Cottonwood Canyon, you'll arrive at Brighton Ski Resort and find the trailhead that begins this beautiful hike to the sister lakes. If you look closely at this photo, first you'll see Lake Mary, followed by Lake Martha, and completing the three sister lakes, Lake Catherine. 

3 years ago I took my first aerial image of these lakes, and returning here and getting an image like this with amazing conditions is a culmination of my 3 years of falling in love with aerial photography.
